<section class="products-section content-section" id="products"><div class="section-heading compact"><span class="kicker">One control system, three instruments</span><h2>Commands. Alarms. Instruments</h2><p>Think of your groups as a plant floor with no instrumentation. Tegsi adds the three layers any control system needs, all sourced from chat your team already lives in.</p></div><div class="product-grid">
<article class="product-card purple"><header><span>Commands · Intake</span><h3>Can Anyone</h3><small>Turn any message into trackable work</small></header><div class="product-body"><p>Anyone posts an ask in the group. Anyone else can claim it, log effort, and mark it complete, right inside the chat.</p><ul><li>ask → claim → effort → complete</li><li>Clear ownership, no message lost</li><li>Mirrored to the web dashboard</li></ul></div></article>
<article class="product-card yellow"><header><span>Alarms · State</span><h3>Action Log</h3><small>Every pending item, every group, one screen</small></header><div class="product-body"><p>Add the bot to your groups and Tegsi harvests every outstanding action into a single control view. Finally know what's stuck across the whole org.</p><ul><li>Cross-group, top-down oversight</li><li>Built for the founder / COO / ops lead</li><li>Value compounds with every group added</li></ul></div></article>
<article class="product-card green"><header><span>Instruments · Metrics</span><h3>Signals</h3><small>Your daily numbers, pulled and reported</small></header><div class="product-body"><p>Define the data points you care about. Tegsi extracts them from chat on a schedule and reports them with the source message one tap away.</p><ul><li>Scheduled daily report, automatic</li><li>Accumulates history → trends &amp; anomalies</li><li>Replaces the morning copy-paste job</li></ul></div></article></div></section>
<section class="engine-section" id="how"><div class="section-heading"><span class="kicker">How it works</span><h2>One engine reads your groups. Every<br>product gets smarter together.</h2><p>Under all three tools sits a single capability, a message understanding layer over your Telegram groups. Build it once, and intake, alarms and instruments all ride on it. That convergence is something Telegram won't build and a generic bot can't match.</p></div><div class="engine-flow"><div><strong>Telegram groups</strong><span>where work already happens</span></div><b>→</b><div><strong>Tegsi engine</strong><span>classify · extract · structure</span></div><b>→</b><div><strong>Control dashboard</strong><span>work · pending · signals</span></div></div></section>
<section class="audience-section content-section"><div class="section-heading compact"><span class="kicker">Who it’s for</span><h2>Adoption from the team. Value for the boss.</h2><p>Tegsi is loved by the people doing the work and paid for by the people who need to see it.</p></div><div class="audience-grid"><article><span>The doer</span><h3>Anyone in the group</h3><p>Drops an ask, claims a task, marks it done, without leaving Telegram. Zero new habits, zero new app. This is what drives adoption across the org.</p></article><article><span>The overseer</span><h3>Founder · COO · Ops lead</h3><p>Gets the one thing they don't have today: visibility. What's pending everywhere, what moved, and the daily numbers, in a control center that becomes part of the morning routine.</p></article></div></section>
